"'''''Kote Darasuum'''''," meaning "Glory Eternal," was an ancient [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] war chant sung in [[Mando'a/Legends|Mando'a]]. During his training of the [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]], [[Jango Fett/Legends|Jango Fett]] revised a number of chants, including "Kote Darasuum," replacing traditional Mandalorian keywords with more appropriate Republic ones, although this short chant required no modifications.<ref name="LA">{{LucasArts|url=games/swrepubliccommando/downloads/mp3s/Lyrics.pdf|text="Star Wars: Republic Commando: English Translation of Ancient Mandalorian Text"}}</ref> Ultimately, the Republic's [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army]] chose ''Darasuum Kote'' as its motto.<ref name="Warfare">''[[The Essential Guide to Warfare]]''</ref>

==Lyrics==
===''[[Mando'a]]''===
Kote, darasuum kote.<br />
Te racin ka'ra juaan kote.<br />

===[[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]]===
Glory, eternal glory.<br />
The stars pale beside our might.<br />

